Topic: SD-WAN

Objectives:
1. Describe SD-WAN.
2. Explain the advantages of using SD-WAN.
3. Understand how SD-WAN technology has evolved.

###
SD-WAN - Software-Defined Wide-Area Network (SD-WAN) is a technology that applies software-defined networking (SDN) principles to improve how wide-area networks connect across different locations.

SD-WAN – Performance and Traffic Management
> Performance Monitoring  
SD-WAN continuously monitors WAN connections to maintain high speeds and optimize connectivity.

> Application-Aware Traffic Routing  
It regulates different types of traffic, reserving high-speed links for critical business applications.

> Support for Modern Applications  
Unlike traditional router-centric WAN, SD-WAN supports apps hosted in:
- On-premises data centers
- Public or private clouds
- SaaS services (e.g., Salesforce, Dropbox, AWS)

